## Work Stream 6 — Persistent Project Memory & Auto-Context

### Strategy
On session start (or IDE startup when a workspace has a prior session), auto-inject the project context as the **first hidden system message** to the agent. This is what Embedder does — the agent knows the project before you type a single character.

#### [NEW] [firmwareProjectMemoryService.ts](file:///Users/sanjaysenthilkumar/Documents/IDE/void/src/vs/workbench/contrib/neuralInverseFirmware/browser/firmwareProjectMemoryService.ts)
A lightweight key-value store backed by `IStorageService` (workspace scope) with:
- `saveProjectMemory(workspaceUri, memory)` — saves project facts (MCU, build system, key files, compile errors)
- `loadProjectMemory(workspaceUri)` — retrieves them on next startup
- `buildContextMessage()` — formats them into the agent's first hidden user turn

#### [MODIFY] [hardwareContextProvider.ts](file:///Users/sanjaysenthilkumar/Documents/IDE/void/src/vs/workbench/contrib/neuralInverseFirmware/browser/engine/hardwareContext/hardwareContextProvider.ts)
Include `projectMemoryService.buildContextMessage()` output at the top of the injected context block, ensuring the agent sees: current MCU, project type, key files detected, last known errors, and previously stored notes.

